What do you get?

Upon subscribing, you will no longer need to worry about the UI part of the code for your Xcode projects & how your app will look on all screen sizes.

  • UI Code
  • Animations
  • Localization
  • Analytics
  • Accessibility
  • UI Bugs Fix

UI Code

UiWorks provides UI Code (views, controls, and layout) code for iOS, visionOS, iPadOS, macOS, watchOS & tvOS in SwiftUI, UIKit, Storyboard, AppKit or WatchKit.

So basically your designer provide designs in AdobeXD, Figma, inVision, Photoshop, Sketch and UiWorks turn these Designs to Codes so you & your dev team never have to worry about how your app will look on different screen sizes.

Frequently asked questions (FAQ)

❶

Why wouldn't I just let developer do these work?

Developers are geniuses, but they're not superheroes. They can do challenging work, but they also have to deal with tedious tasks like adjusting layout and text for different screen sizes. Outsourcing these tasks to UiWorks can improve the overall development process and save you time and money.

❶

When should you subscribe to UiWorks?

Once you have atleast one screen designed for your mobile app.

❷

Is there a limit to how many requests I can have?

Once I get your project access, you're able to add as many tasks/requests to your queue as you'd like, and they will be delivered one by one.

❸

How fast will I receive code changes?

On average, most requests are completed in just 2-3 days or less. However, more complex requests or lengthy tasks can take longer..

❹

Who are the developer?

You might be surprised to hear this, but UiWorks is actually an agency of one. This means you'll work directly with me, founder of UiWorks. However, for some request such as custom animations or custom implementation I partner with expert developer.

❺

How does the pause feature work?

We understand you may not have enough development work to fill up entire month. Perhaps you only have one or two development tasks at the moment. That's where pausing your subscription comes in handy. Billing cycles are based on 31 day period. Let's say you sign up and use the service for 21 days, and then decide to pause your subscription. This means that the billing cycle will be paused and you'll have 10 days of service remaining to be used anytime in the future.

❻

What programming languages use for all UI realted works?

All development is in Swift or Objective-C and some standard library like lotties.

❼

How do I raise requests for work?

You create tasks in trello board or send an email.

❽

What if I don't like code standards?

No worries! I'll continue to refactor or rewrite the code as per your set of guidelines, best practices, programming styles and conventions that you or your developers follow when writing code for a project

❾

What if I only have a single request?

That's fine. You can pause your subscription when finished and return when you have additional work needs. There's no need to let the remainder of your subscription go to waste..

𝟏𝟎

Are there any refunds if I don't like service?

You can cancel your subscription at anytime but due quality nature of work, there will be no refunds issued.
